Definition: [τοιοῦτος] (including the other inflections); from {{g5104}} and {{g3778}}; truly this, i.e. of this sort (to denote character or individuality)
[τοῖχος] another form of {{g5038}}; a wall
[τοί] probably for the dative case of {{g3588}}; an enclitic particle of asseveration by way of contrast; in sooth)
[τοιγαροῦν] from {{g5104}} and {{g1063}} and {{g3767}}; truly for then, i.e. consequently
[τοίνυν] from {{g5104}} and {{g3568}}; truly now, i.e. accordingly
[τοιόσδε] (including the other inflections); from a derivative of 5104 and {{g1161}}; such-like then, i.e. so great
[τίς] probably emphatic of {{g5100}}; an interrogative pronoun, who, which or what (in direct or indirect questions)
[τίτλος] of Latin origin; a titulus or "title" (placard)
[Τίτος] of Latin origin but uncertain significance; Titus, a Christian

[τύπος] from {{g5180}}; a die (as struck), i.e. (by implication) a stamp or scar; by analogy, a shape, i.e. a statue, (figuratively) style or resemblance; specially, a sampler ("type"), i.e. a model (for imitation) or instance (for warning)
[τυμπανίζω] from a derivative of {{g5180}} (meaning a drum, "tympanum"); to stretch on an instrument of torture resembling a drum, and thus beat to death
[τρυφάω] from {{g5172}}; to indulge in luxury
[Τρύφαινα] from {{g5172}}; luxurious; Tryphæna, a Christian woman
[Τρυφῶσα] from {{g5172}}; luxuriating; Tryphosa, a Christian female
[τρυφή] from θρύπτω (to break up or (figuratively) enfeeble, especially the mind and body by indulgence); effeminacy, i.e. luxury or debauchery
[Τρωγύλλιον] of uncertain derivation; Trogyllium, a place in Asia Minor
[Τρωάς] from Τρός (a Trojan); the Troad (or plain of Troy), i.e. Troas, a place in Asia Minor

[τυγχάνω] probably for an obsolete τύχω (for which the middle voice of another alternate τεύχω (to make ready or bring to pass) is used in certain tenses; akin to the base of {{g5088}} through the idea of effecting; properly, to affect; or (specially), to hit or light upon (as a mark to be reached), i.e. (transitively) to attain or secure an object or end, or (intransitively) to happen (as if meeting with); but in the latter application only impersonal (with {{g1487}}), i.e. perchance; or (present participle) as adjective, usual (as if commonly met with, with {{g3756}}, extraordinary), neuter (as adverb) perhaps; or (with another verb) as adverb, by accident (as it were) Compare {{g5180}}.

[τρώγω] probably strengthened from a collateral form of the base of {{g5134}} and {{g5147}} through the idea of corrosion or wear; or perhaps rather of a base of {{g5167}} and {{g5149}} through the idea of a craunching sound; to gnaw or chew, i.e. (generally) to eat
[Τύρος] of Hebrew origin ({{h6865}}): Tyrus (i.e. Tsor), a place in Palestine
[τυφλός] from, {{g5187}}; opaque (as if smoky), i.e. (by analogy) blind (physically or mentally)
[τυφλόω] from {{g5185}}; to make blind, i.e. (figuratively) to obscure
[τυφόω] from a derivative of {{g5188}}; to envelop with smoke, i.e. (figuratively) to inflate with self-conceit

[τύπτω] a primary verb (in a strengthened form); to "thump", i.e. cudgel or pummel (properly, with a stick or bastinado), but in any case by repeated blows; thus differing from {{g3817}} and {{g3960}}, which denote a (usually single) blow with the hand or any instrument, or {{g4141}} with the fist (or a hammer), or {{g4474}} with the palm; as well as from {{g5177}}, an accidental collision); by implication, to punish; figuratively, to offend (the conscience)
[Τύραννος] a provincial form of the derivative of the base of {{g2962}}; a "tyrant"; Tyrannus, an Ephesian
[τυρβάζω] from τύρβη (Latin , a crowd; akin to {{g2351}}); to make "turbid", i.e. disturb
[Τύριος] from {{g5184}}; a Tyrian, i.e. inhabitant of Tyrus
[τύφω] apparently a primary verb; to make a smoke, i.e. slowly consume without flame
[τυφωνικός] from a derivative of {{g5188}}; stormy (as if smoky)
[τρυμαλιά] from a derivative of τρύω (to wear away; akin to the base of {{g5134}}, {{g5147}} and {{g5176}}); an orifice, i.e. needle's eye Compare {{g5169}}.
[τρύπημα] from a derivative of the base of {{g5168}}; an aperture, i.e. a needle's eye
[τροφός] from {{g5142}}; a nourisher, i.e. nurse
[τροχιά] from {{g5164}}; a track (as a wheel-rut), i.e. (figuratively) a course of conduct
[τροφή] from {{g5142}}; nourishment (literally or figuratively); by implication, rations (wages)
[Τρόφιμος] from {{g5160}}; nutritive; Trophimus, a Christian
[τρυγάω] from a derivative of τρύγω (to dry) meaning ripe fruit (as if dry); to collect the vintage
[τρυγών] from τρύζω (to murmur; akin to {{g5149}}, but denoting a duller sound); a turtle-dove (as cooing)
[τροχός] from {{g5143}}; a wheel (as a runner), i.e. (figuratively) a circuit of physical effects
[τρύβλιον] neuter of a presumed derivative of uncertain affinity; a bowl
[τροπή] from an apparently primary τρέπω to turn; a turn ("trope"), i.e. revolution (figuratively, variation)
[τρόμος] from {{g5141}}; a "trembling", i.e. quaking with fear
[τρίχινος] from {{g2359}}; hairy, i.e. made of hair (mohair)
[τρίτος] ordinal from {{g5140}}; third; neuter (as noun) a third part, or (as adverb) a (or the) third time, thirdly
[τρισχίλιοι] from {{g5151}} and {{g5507}}; three times a thousand
[τρίστεγον] neuter of a compound of {{g5140}} and {{g4721}} as noun; a third roof (story)
[τρίς] adverb from {{g5140}}; three times
[τρίμηνον] neuter of a compound of {{g5140}} and {{g3376}} as noun; a three months' space
[τροποφορέω] from {{g5158}} and {{g5409}}; to endure one's habits
[τρόπος] from the same as {{g5157}}; a turn, i.e. (by implication) mode or style (especially with preposition or relative prefix as adverb, like); figuratively, deportment or character
[τρεῖς] ,   or neuter      τρίαa primary (plural) number; "three"
[τρέμω] strengthened from a primary τρέω (to "dread", "terrify"); to "tremble" or fear

[τρέφω] a primary verb (properly, τρέφω; but perhaps strengthened from the base of {{g5157}} through the idea of convolution); properly, to stiffen, i.e. fatten (by implication, to cherish (with food, etc.), pamper, rear)
[τρέχω] apparently a primary verb (properly, θρέχω; compare {{g2359}}); which uses δρέμω (the base of {{g1408}}) as alternate in certain tenses; to run or walk hastily (literally or figuratively)
[τριάκοντα] the decade of {{g5140}}; thirty
[τριακόσιοι] plural from {{g5140}} and {{g1540}}; three hundred
[τρίβολος] from {{g5140}} and {{g956}}; properly, a crow-foot (three-pronged obstruction in war), i.e. (by analogy) a thorny plant (caltrop)
[τρίβος] from τρίβω (to "rub"; akin to τείρω, τρύω, and the base of {{g5131}}, {{g5134}}); a rut or worn track
[τριετία] from a compound of {{g5140}} and {{g2094}}; a three years' period (triennium)
[τρίζω] apparently a primary verb; to creak (squeak), i.e. (by analogy) to grate the teeth (in frenzy)
[τραυματίζω] from {{g5134}}; to inflict a wound
[τραῦμα] from the base of τιτρώσκω (to wound; akin to the base of {{g2352}}, {{g5147}}, {{g5149}}, etc.); a wound
[τράχηλος] probably from {{g5143}} (through the idea of mobility); the throat (neck), i.e. (figuratively) life
[τραχηλίζω] from {{g5137}}; to seize by the throat or neck, i.e. to expose the gullet of a victim for killing (generally, to lay bare)
[τράγος] from the base of {{g5176}}; a he-goat (as a gnawer)
[τούτων] genitive case plural masculine or neuter of {{g3778}}; of (from or concerning) these (persons or things)
[τραπεζίτης] from {{g5132}}; a money-broker or banker

[τράπεζα] probably contracted from {{g5064}} and {{g3979}}; a table or stool (as being four-legged), usually for food (figuratively, a meal); also a counter for money (figuratively, a broker's office for loans at interest)
[Τραχωνῖτις] from a derivative of {{g5138}}; rough district; Trachonitis, a region of Syria
[τραχύς] perhaps strengthened from the base of {{g4486}} (as if jagged by rents); uneven, rocky (reefy)
[ὑγρός] from the base of {{g5205}}; wet (as if with rain), i.e. (by implication) sappy (fresh)
[τοῦτον] accusative case singular masculine of {{g3778}}; this (person, as objective of verb or preposition)
[τούτου] genitive case singular masculine or neuter of {{g3778}}; of (from or concerning) this (person or thing)
[τοῦτο] neuter singular nominative or accusative case of {{g3778}}; that thing
[τούτοις] dative case plural masculine or neuter of {{g3778}}; to (for, in, with or by) these (persons or things)
[τοὔνομα] contraction for the neuter of {{g3588}} and {{g3686}}; the name (is)
[τουτέστι] contraction for {{g5124}} and {{g2076}}; that is
[τοῦ] properly, the genitive case of {{g3588}}; sometimes used for {{g5127}}; of this person
[τοὐναντίον] contraction for the neuter of {{g3588}} and {{g1726}}; on the contrary
[τούτους] accusative case plural masculine of {{g3778}}; these (persons, as objective of verb or preposition)
[τούτῳ] dative case singular masculine or neuter of {{g3778}}; to (in, with or by) this (person or thing)
[ὑγιής] from the base of {{g837}}; healthy, i.e. well (in body); figuratively, true (in doctrine)
[ὑγιαίνω] from {{g5199}}; to have sound health, i.e. be well (in body); figuratively, to be uncorrupt (true in doctrine)
[ὑάλινος] from {{g5194}}; glassy, i.e. transparent
[ὑάκινθος] of uncertain derivation; the "hyacinth" or "jacinth", i.e. some gem of a deep blue color, probably the zirkon
[ὑακίνθινος] from {{g5192}}; "hyacinthine" or "jacinthine", i.e. deep blue
[Τυχικός] from a derivative of {{g5177}}; fortuitous, i.e. fortunate; Tychicus, a Christian
[ὑβριστής] from {{g5195}}; an insulter, i.e. maltreater
[ὕβρις] from {{g5228}}; insolence (as over-bearing), i.e. insult, injury
[ὑβρίζω] from {{g5196}}; to exercise violence, i.e. abuse
[ὕαλος] perhaps from the same as {{g5205}} (as being transparent like rain); glass
[τολμητής] from {{g5111}}; a daring (audacious) man
[τολμηρότερον] neuter of the compound of a derivative of the base of 5111 (as adverb); more daringly, i.e. with greater confidence than otherwise

[τολμάω] from τόλμα (boldness; probably itself from the base of {{g5056}} through the idea of extreme conduct); to venture (objectively or in act; while {{g2292}} is rather subjective or in feeling); by implication, to be courageous
[τόκος] from the base of {{g5088}}; interest on money loaned (as a produce)

[τόπος] apparently a primary word; a spot (general in space, but limited by occupancy; whereas {{g5561}} is a large but participle locality), i.e. location (as a position, home, tract, etc.); figuratively, condition, opportunity; specially, a scabbard
[τοπάζιον] neuter of a presumed derivative (alternately) of τόπαζος (a "topaz"; of uncertain origin); a gem, probably the chrysolite
[τόξον] from the base of {{g5088}}; a bow (apparently as the simplest fabric)

[τομώτερος] comparative of a derivative of the primary τέμνω (to cut; more comprehensive or decisive than {{g2875}}, as if by a single stroke; whereas that implies repeated blows, like hacking); more keen
[τότε] from (the neuter of) {{g3588}} and {{g3753}}; the when, i.e. at the time that (of the past or future, also in consecution)
[τοσοῦτος] from τόσος (so much; apparently from {{g3588}} and {{g3739}}) and {{g3778}} (including its variations); so vast as this, i.e. such (in quantity, amount, number of space)
